The evidence with the title 'Debt ceiling: definition, current status ' says The debt ceiling is a limit on how much debt the U.S. government can have.  ... When it refuses to increase the debt limit , it 's saying it wants to spend but not pay its bills .  ... It 's a last resort to get attention by the non-majority in Congress.  ... Congress did not vote on the debt ceiling , focusing instead on Trump 's tax bill. 
